    DccNiTghmare is a  program registered in public domain, do
whatever  you  want  with  its  code  and  data.

==============================================================
|                         DccNiTghtmare                      |
==============================================================

I   - Requeriments
II  - Instalation
III - Execution
IV  - Contacts

==============================================================
|                      I - Requeriments                      |
==============================================================

   The DccNiTghtmare's compilation and execution needs some 
software and hardware. They are:

   Software:
   OpenGL   - Mesa3D 6.2, www.mesa3d.org (or SGI-OpenGL 1.4)
   SDL      - Version 1.2.7, www.libsdl.org
   SDLimage - Version 1.2.4, www.libsdl.org/projects/SDL_image/

   Hardware:
   Video Card with 3D aceleration, OpenGl compatible in Linux.

==============================================================
|                      II - Instalation                      |
==============================================================

1) Source-Code Distribution

   a) LINUX   

   To   "install"   dccnitghtmare,   decompact   the  tar.bz2,  
go to the directory dccnitghtmare and run "make".
   Exemple:
   farrer@anamabeka:~/$ tar -xvjf dccnitghtmare.tar.bz2
   farrer@anamabeka:~/$ cd dccnitghtmare
   farrer@anamabeka:~/dccnitghtmare/$ make

   b) WINDOWS

   To  compile  dccnitghtmare  on  windows,  you'll  need  the 
dev-c++  compiler  (a.k.a. gcc port and ide to Windows).  Open
the project DccNiTghtmare.dev on it and compile.

2) Binary Distribution

    Only decompact the archive you downloaded.

==============================================================
|                       III - Execution                       |
==============================================================

   To execute  the  program,  go to directory ./bin and run the 
file dccnitghtmare. It's needed  to be on X. We really hope the
game  will  open in  this case, and  the  interation-navigation 
follows:

                 ========================
                 | Camera Movimentation |
                 ========================

mouse at left corner  =  turn camera                  (0-360°)
left arrow            =  turn camera left             (0-360°)
mouse at right corner =  turn camera                  (0-360°)
right arrow           =  turn camera right            (0-360°)
up arrow              =  increases zoom               (X-Ym)
down arrow            =  decreases zoom               (X-Ym)
home                  =  maximize zoom
end                   =  minimize zoom
pageup                =  camera up                    (0-89°)
pagedown              =  camera down                  (0-89°)
insert                =  put camera on the top
delete                =  put camera on the floor

              ===========================
              | Character Movimentation |
              ===========================

a          =  turn left                       (0-360°)
d          =  turn right                      (0-360°)
w          =  forward                         (0-?)
s          =  backward                        (0-?)
q          =  move left                       (0-?)
e          =  move right                      (0-?)
tab        =  make active next character 
lctrl+tab  =  make active previous character
 
                    =====================
                    | Auxiliars Windows |
                    =====================

m      =  Open MiniMap window
n      =  Open ShortCut window

   To  end  the  game,  simple  press  ESC key,  and  click on 
button exit.

